title: Dwenger tops Snider, controls SAC title picture, The Score for Oct. 9
text:
Dwenger tops Snider, controls SAC title picture, The Score for Oct. 9 
By Dean Pantazi -21Alive October 10, 2015 Updated Oct 10, 2015 at 12:00 AM EDT 
UNDATED (21 Alive) - Amaun Clark rans for 203 yards and two touchdowns and caught a pass for a third as Dwenger handed Snider its first loss of the season 20-17 on Friday night. 
The win puts both the Saints and Panthers at 7-1 in the Summit Athletic Conference, but because Dwenger won, they own the tiebreaker, and thus win the conference by beating winless Wayne next week. 
Landon Durnell ran for 143 yards and two touchdowns and Ben Skowronek had a touchdown catch and one of two key Homestead interceptions on defense as the Spartans knocked off Luers 28-2. 
A key was Homestead holding Knights star Austin Mack to a total of 69 offensive yards. 
East Noble put itself in position to play for a share of the first Northeast 8 title with their 54-20 win over New Haven. 
It sets up the showdown with Bellmont next week at East Noble, as the Braves remained perfect in the NE 8 with their 28-6 win over DeKalb. 
There is also a Week 9 title showdown set in the Allen County Atthletic Conference between Woodlan and Adams Central. 
Woodlan got 159 yards and two touchdowns on the ground from Mitchell VanBrocklin as the Warrios stayed perfect at 808 with their 37-0 blanking of South Adams 
Adams Central also is now 8-0 with their 23-0 whitewash of Bluffton, as Drew Schultz ran for two touchdowns, Bailey Hurst totaled 123 yards on the ground, and Andrew Hammon threw for a touchdown. 
The game will be played at Adams Central.
